               <p>In his Defence he said he was hir'd to carry those Goods, by a Man that stood at the Brasier's Door who he thought belong'd to the House. But he could bring no Proof of it, nor why he run so fast, and when he dropt the Goods did not stay to take them up again. <rs id="t17260114-20-verdict121" type="verdictDescription">
